General Assembly Proposed Bill No. 5172
February Session, 2026 LCO No. 961
Referred to Committee on APPROPRIATIONS
Introduced by:
REP. DILLON, 92nd Dist.
AN ACT CONCERNING FUNDING FOR THE INSTALLATION AND
MAINTENANCE OF RADAR SPEED SIGNS ON FOREST ROAD IN THE
CITY OF NEW HAVEN.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General
Assembly convened:
1 That the sum of ___ dollars be appropriated to the Department of
2 Transportation for the fiscal year ending June 30, 2027, for the
3 installation and maintenance of radar speed signs alongside Forest Road
4 in the city of New Haven.
Statement of Purpose:
To reduce speeding and increase safety on Forest Road in the city of
New Haven.
